  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2000 Trees To Save Community Water Source in Abuja</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kpanyi-Kpanyi village in Gosa along Airport Road in Abuja, houses over 300 households, borders Gosa River. Though located within the Federal Capital City,lacks access to portable source of water. Cases of blood in the urine have been reported from usage of Gosa River.The suitable streams are rapidly drying up due to excessive cutting of  trees protecting the water shed for fuel wood. Planting of 2000 trees along the water cause will save the suitable streams serving the community from drying up</narrative>
  </description>
